    <p class="about-us-desc">
      <span class="fw-bold">Teach Me</span> is a web platform which puts a termination in hiring tutors traditionally. It's a middleware between tutors and students. The main focus of it is to provide some extra income to the tutors as well as to offer a cost effective learning path to the students. Now, a student can hire a tutor by hours. Maybe he's stuck with some math problems or finding it difficult to understand a specific chapter or lesson, he can jump into <span class="fw-bold">Teach Me</span> to post his problems. The highly qualified tutors may respond to his post by writing a quote to get hired by the specific student for a single hour to many. Students are going to be happy as they need no longer to unnecessarily keep  a tutors for months. He can just hire tutors for what he wants and when he wants. Tutors are also finding it useful. A tutor who already offers 5/6 tuitions, should find it difficult to offer a new one. What he can do is to find some hourly jobs in his free time which can also genearte a handome income by the end of the month.
